Secretary of the Interior Ken Salazar and Assistant to the President for Energy and Climate Change Carol Browner held a briefing to discuss the 6 month moratorium on exploratory deepwater drilling and the implementation of new safety measures for offshore oil and gas drilling. The briefing took place on May 27 at 3:00 PM EDT. The purpose of the briefing was to address the moratorium and the measures being taken to ensure the safety of offshore drilling. Reporters were invited to participate via a conference call.